                    <li>Basic database terminology and concepts</li>
                    <li>The relationship between databases and web applications</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üèóÔ∏è What is a Database?</h2>
                
                <svg class="database-icon" viewBox="0 0 100 100">
                    <ellipse cx="50" cy="20" rx="35" ry="15" fill="#667eea" opacity="0.8"/>
                    <rect x="15" y="20" width="70" height="40" fill="#667eea" opacity="0.6"/>
                    <ellipse cx="50" cy="60" rx="35" ry="15" fill="#667eea" opacity="0.8"/>
                    <rect x="15" y="60" width="70" height="20" fill="#667eea" opacity="0.4"/>
                    <ellipse cx="50" cy="80" rx="35" ry="15" fill="#667eea" opacity="0.6"/>
                </svg>

                <p>Imagine a database as a <strong>digital filing cabinet</strong> üìÅ - but one that's incredibly smart, fast, and never forgets where it put things!</p>

                <div class="real-world-example">
                    <h3>üåç Real-World Analogy: The Library System</h3>
                    <p>Think of a library:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Books</strong> = Your data (user information, posts, products)</li>
                        <li><strong>Card Catalog</strong> = Database index (helps find things quickly)</li>
                        <li><strong>Librarian</strong> = Database Management System (organizes and retrieves)</li>
                        <li><strong>Library Rules</strong> = Database constraints (keeps data organized)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üìä Why Do We Need Databases?</h2>
                
                <canvas id="dataGrowthCanvas" class="database-animation" width="600" height="300"></canvas>
                <script>
                    const ctx = document.getElementById('dataGrowthCanvas').getContext('2d');
                    let dataPoints = 1;
                    
                    function drawDataGrowth() {
                        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, 600, 300);
                        
                        // Draw title
                        ctx.font = '16px Arial';
                        ctx.fillStyle = '#333';
                        ctx.fillText('Website Data Growth Over Time', 200, 30);
                        
                        // Draw axes
                        ctx.beginPath();
                        ctx.moveTo(50, 250);
                        ctx.lineTo(550, 250);
                        ctx.moveTo(50, 50);
                        ctx.lineTo(50, 250);
                        ctx.stroke();
                        
                        // Draw data points
                        ctx.fillStyle = '#667eea';
                        for (let i = 0; i < dataPoints; i++) {
                            let x = 50 + (i * 10);
                            let y = 250 - (Math.pow(i, 1.5) * 2);
                            ctx.fillRect(x - 2, y, 4, 250 - y);
                        }
                        
                        if (dataPoints < 50) {
                            dataPoints++;
                            setTimeout(drawDataGrowth, 100);
                        }
                    }
                    drawDataGrowth();
                </script>

                <h3>Problems Databases Solve:</h3>
                <div class="problem-solution-grid">
                    <div class="problem-card">
                        <h4>‚ùå Without a Database</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Files scattered everywhere</li>
                            <li>Duplicate information</li>
                            <li>Slow searches through data</li>
                            <li>No data relationships</li>
                            <li>Security nightmares</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="solution-card">
                        <h4>‚úÖ With a Database</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Organized, centralized storage</li>
                            <li>Single source of truth</li>
                            <li>Lightning-fast queries</li>
                            <li>Complex relationships</li>
                            <li>Built-in security features</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üé≠ Types of Databases</h2>
                
                <table class="comparison-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Type</th>
                            <th>Structure</th>
                            <th>Best For</th>
                            <th>Examples</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Relational (SQL)</strong> üóÉÔ∏è</td>
                            <td>Tables with rows and columns</td>
                            <td>Structured data, complex relationships</td>
                            <td>MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQLite</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>NoSQL</strong> üìÑ</td>
                            <td>Documents, key-value pairs</td>
                            <td>Flexible data, rapid development</td>
                            <td>MongoDB, Redis, Firebase</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Graph</strong> üï∏Ô∏è</td>
                            <td>Nodes and relationships</td>
                            <td>Social networks, recommendations</td>
                            <td>Neo4j, Amazon Neptune</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Time-Series</strong> ‚è∞</td>
                            <td>Time-stamped data</td>
                            <td>IoT, monitoring, analytics</td>
                            <td>InfluxDB, TimescaleDB</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üèõÔ∏è Database Architecture</h2>
                
                <div class="mermaid">
                    graph TB
                        A[Web Browser] -->|HTTP Request| B[Web Server]
                        B -->|PHP/Application| C[Application Layer]
                        C -->|SQL Queries| D[Database Server]
                        D -->|Data Results| C
                        C -->|HTML Response| B
                        B -->|Web Page| A
                        
                        style A fill:#f0f9ff,stroke:#0891b2
                        style B fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#f59e0b
                        style C fill:#ede9fe,stroke:#8b5cf6
                        style D fill:#f0fdf4,stroke:#10b981
                </div>

                <div class="real-world-example">
                    <h3>üçï Real-World Example: Pizza Ordering System</h3>
                    <p>When you order pizza online:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li><strong>You (Browser)</strong>: "I want a large pepperoni pizza"</li>
                        <li><strong>Website (Server)</strong>: "Let me check what we have"</li>
                        <li><strong>Kitchen System (Application)</strong>: "Database, do we have pepperoni?"</li>
                        <li><strong>Inventory (Database)</strong>: "Yes! 50 portions available"</li>
                        <li><strong>Kitchen System</strong>: "Order confirmed, preparing now"</li>
                        <li><strong>Website</strong>: "Your pizza will arrive in 30 minutes!"</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üìö Essential Database Terms</h2>
                
                <canvas id="databaseStructureCanvas" width="600" height="400"></canvas>
                <script>
                    const dbCtx = document.getElementById('databaseStructureCanvas').getContext('2d');
                    
                    // Draw database structure visualization
                    dbCtx.fillStyle = '#667eea';
                    dbCtx.fillRect(50, 50, 500, 40);
                    dbCtx.fillStyle = 'white';
                    dbCtx.font = 'bold 18px Arial';
                    dbCtx.fillText('DATABASE: online_store', 200, 75);
                    
                    // Draw tables
                    const tables = ['users', 'products', 'orders'];
                    tables.forEach((table, index) => {
                        let x = 50 + (index * 180);
                        
                        // Table header
                        dbCtx.fillStyle = '#8b5cf6';
                        dbCtx.fillRect(x, 120, 150, 30);
                        dbCtx.fillStyle = 'white';
                        dbCtx.font = '14px Arial';
                        dbCtx.fillText(`TABLE: ${table}`, x + 40, 140);
                        
                        // Table rows
                        const rows = [
                            ['id', 'name', 'email'],
                            ['1', 'John', 'john@ex...'],
                            ['2', 'Jane', 'jane@ex...']
                        ];
                        
                        rows.forEach((row, rowIndex) => {
                            let y = 160 + (rowIndex * 25);
                            dbCtx.fillStyle = rowIndex === 0 ? '#e5e7eb' : '#f9fafb';
                            dbCtx.fillRect(x, y, 150, 25);
                            
                            dbCtx.fillStyle = rowIndex === 0 ? '#374151' : '#6b7280';
                            dbCtx.font = rowIndex === 0 ? 'bold 11px Arial' : '11px Arial';
                            
                            row.forEach((cell, cellIndex) => {
                                dbCtx.fillText(cell, x + 5 + (cellIndex * 50), y + 17);
                            });
                        });
                    });
                    
                    // Draw relationships
                    dbCtx.strokeStyle = '#10b981';
                    dbCtx.lineWidth = 2;
                    dbCtx.setLineDash([5, 5]);
                    dbCtx.beginPath();
                    dbCtx.moveTo(200, 235);
                    dbCtx.lineTo(230, 235);
                    dbCtx.stroke();
                    
                    dbCtx.beginPath();
                    dbCtx.moveTo(380, 235);
                    dbCtx.lineTo(410, 235);
                    dbCtx.stroke();
                </script>

                <div class="terminology-grid">
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <h3>üóÑÔ∏è Database</h3>
                        <p>A container that holds all your tables and data. Like a filing cabinet.</p>
                        <code>CREATE DATABASE my_website;</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <h3>üìã Table</h3>
                        <p>A collection of related data organized in rows and columns. Like a spreadsheet.</p>
                        <code>CREATE TABLE users (...);</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <h3>üìù Record/Row</h3>
                        <p>A single entry in a table. Like one person's complete information.</p>
                        <code>INSERT INTO users VALUES (...);</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <h3>üìä Column/Field</h3>
                        <p>A specific piece of information. Like "name" or "email" for all users.</p>
                        <code>SELECT name, email FROM users;</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <h3>üîë Primary Key</h3>
                        <p>A unique identifier for each record. Like a social security number.</p>
                        <code>id INT PRIMARY KEY</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="term-card">
                        <h3>üîó Foreign Key</h3>
                        <p>Links tables together. Like a reference number connecting an order to a customer.</p>
                        <code>user_id INT FOREIGN KEY</code>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>üåê Databases in WordPress</h2>
                
                <div class="mermaid">
                    graph LR
                        A[WordPress Site] --> B[wp_posts]
                        A --> C[wp_users]
                        A --> D[wp_comments]
                        A --> E[wp_options]
                        A --> F[wp_postmeta]
                        A --> G[wp_usermeta]
                        
                        B --> H[Blog Posts]
                        B --> I[Pages]
                        C --> J[Authors]
                        C --> K[Subscribers]
                        D --> L[User Comments]
                        E --> M[Site Settings]
                        
                        style A fill:#f0f9ff,stroke:#0891b2
                        style B fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#f59e0b
                        style C fill:#ede9fe,stroke:#8b5cf6
                </div>

                <p>WordPress uses MySQL to store:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>üìù <strong>Posts and Pages</strong>: All your content</li>
                    <li>üë• <strong>Users</strong>: Account information and roles</li>
                    <li>üí¨ <strong>Comments</strong>: User interactions</li>
                    <li>‚öôÔ∏è <strong>Settings</strong>: Configuration and options</li>
                    <li>üé® <strong>Theme Data</strong>: Customizations and preferences</li>
                    <li>üîå <strong>Plugin Data</strong>: Extended functionality</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

